an politician)|Jim McGovern]], U.S. Representative (MA-2nd)<ref name=bostonglobe>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2019/08/15/majority-mass-members-congress-backing-markey/TIfPrMNTQzyqjQgulZ1ShP/story.html|title=Majority of Mass. members of Congress backing Ed Markey\u2019s reelection bid|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|author=Joshua Miller|date=August 15, 2019|accessdate=September 12, 2019}}</ref> \n* [[Richard Neal]], U.S. Representative (MA-1st)<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"/>\n* [[Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez]], U.S. Representative (NY-14th)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boston.com/news/politics/2019/09/13/alexandria-ocasio-cortez-endorses-ed-markey-reelection|title=Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez endorses Ed Markey for reelection|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|date=September 13, 2019|accessdate=September 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Lori Trahan]], U.S. Representative (MA-3rd)<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"/>\n\n;Statewide politicians\n* [[Michael Dukakis]], [[1988 United States presidential election|1988 Democratic Presidential Nominee]], former [[Governor of Massachusetts]] (1975\u20131979, 1983\u20131991)<ref>{{cite article|last=McGrane|first=Victoria|title=Michael Dukakis endorses Ed Markey in Democratic Senate primary race|date=January 28, 2020|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/2020/01/28/metro/michael-dukakis-endorses-ed-markey-senate-primary-race/|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n;State officials\n* [[James Arciero]], State Representative<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[Brian Ashe]], State Representative<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[Bruce Ayers]], State Representative<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[Ruth Balser]], State Representative<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[Christine Barber]], State Representative<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[John Barrett (Massachusetts politician)|John Barrett]], State Representative<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[Michael J. Barrett]], State Senator<ref name =\"StateLegMarkey\"/>\n* [[Jennif